TAP

TAP

TAP

Your ears perk up as you hear something.  Something is shuffling outside the shed, testing the walls, tap tap tapping.  You see a long finger, red at the tip, tap at the grimy windowpane, then withdraw.  A moment later, the shed door rattles but whatever is out there doesn't seem to understand the doorknob -- it's just blundering against the closed door, its breathing becoming ragged and agitated.

It stops.  And then you hear a thin, rasping voice -- rough and scratchy like branches scraping against a tin roof.

"sssmell blood blood blood. blood sso strong, fresh, good. blood inside..."

The door rattles again. Then the shuffling footsteps and ragged panting recede into the distance until all you can hear is the rain.

