You dive back into the bushes, but you don't have to wait long.  It only takes a few minutes before you hear that familiar snuffling, wheezing breathing sound and a tell-tale TAP TAP TAP.

You shrink back as you see the creature come into view: a long tall thin almost human figure, but just a little too long, too tall, too thin.  You can barely make out any features in the dark, but you see two tiny, beady black eyes reflecting in the gloom and occasionally, when it moves into the reflected glow of a mushroom, you catch sight of raw, red flayed flesh.  Its arms hang at its sides -- too low, long red claws grazing the ground as it starts to shuffle, now jog, now sprinting like a deer across the clearing, straight for your decoy.

It connects and knocks the jack o'lantern head clean off.  For a moment it pauses, but the flying head bounces against the face of the Ravenous Maw, triggering the sticky tendrils to start flailing.

The creature slashes back with its long red claws, shrieking, but the tendrils are whipping about so fast you can't see anything other than a writhing mass.  They start to withdraw, pulling the squirming mass into the waiting maw.   And then, without a sound, it's gone, pulled into that maw and down into the throat, never to return.

With the creeper out of the way you can now concentrate on helping the ghost boy...and also give some thought to remembering your name. Perhaps both are linked?

There are mushrooms everywhere.

You can see a ravenous maw and a detached tendril.
