You toss the raccoon carcass at the spider, hoping this might make a tasty (and distracting) meal for this giant disgusting arachnid.  The spider fliches at first, but quickly recovers.  It scuttles over to the raccoon, grabs it up in its pedipalps and immediately begins... well, you don't have the stomach to watch how the spider eats, but suffice to say your plan worked.

You hear a dull thud as the spider drops the object it was clutching in its pedipalps to grab the raccoon carcass.  It scuttles away into the gloom.
