> open front door

> open front door
It's time to go.  This house isn't real.  Dad isn't your dad. Mom isn't your mom. Jamie isn't your sister, Davey isn't your brother, Ginger isn't even your cat.  All those memories, all those names, you took them from Jeremy, took them to build this house, so he could come visit you in his dreams, so you could get a little touch of the light shining down from light world.

But it's not real. And it's not yours.

You push open the door and look outside.  All you see is darkness, but somehow you don't have any trouble seeing. Now that you remember who you are, what you are, the dark doesn't seem so dark.  Your eyes can see just fine.  You can see your reflection in the glass window by the door -- your orange cat eyes look back at you.

But you're not ready for the dark.  You still crave the light and you know that you're not going to stop looking for it.  You know it won't be easy; it'll take a lot more than just building a house from someone else's dream fragments.  But somehow, someday, you'll build a house of your own.  Somehow, someday, you'll find a way to be in the light.  You'll find your way.

Nothing's in your way now.

You step out onto the front stoop, take one last look behind you at the house you built, and then step out into the dark.

Good luck out there.

[state=Finished]
